Package: msaviz
Title: Multiple Sequence Alignment Visualization
Version: 1.3.0
Authors@R:
    person(c("Benjamin", "Jean-Marie"), "Tremblay", , "benjmtremblay@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7441-2951"))
URL: https://github.com/bjmt/msaviz
BugReports: https://github.com/bjmt/msaviz/issues
Description: Reshapes multiple sequence alignments into tidy data frames
    and renders them as 'ggplot2' heatmaps or per-sequence lollipop charts,
    optionally composed with a percent-identity track, a
    hierarchical-clustering dendrogram, and row or column group annotation
    strips. Includes PNG rasterization for compact output on alignments
    with millions of cells, default colour palettes for DNA, RNA, and
    amino acid alphabets, and standalone command-line scripts for
    one-shot heatmap or lollipop rendering. The visualization approach was
    first used in Hodgins et al. (2023) <doi:10.1038/s41467-023-41174-0>.
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0)
Imports: ggplot2, rlang, grid, tibble, grDevices, methods, png, utils,
    patchwork
